<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-25T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-25T05:00:00-05:00" n="239" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d239">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2429</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-25T11:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1916, 11 a. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received February 26, 2.10 p.
                                    m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3528. Learn on good authority that Foreign Office here was informed
                                that <persName corresp="#p_ZBE1">Baron Zwiedinek</persName>,
                                Austro-Hungarian Chargé d’Affaires, had cabled his Government prior
                                to issue of German memorandum about armed merchant vessels that you
                                personally had informed him that declaration of that nature from
                                Central powers would be welcomed by you.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>